Sports Scene's special Beijing 2022 series "One Minute, One Sport" introduces all the 15 disciplines that make up this edition of the Winter Olympics. In this episode, we focus on snowboarding. Beijing 2022 will see three-time Olympic men's halfpipe gold medalist Shaun White from the United States take part in his fifth but also last Olympics, and China's 17-year-old Su Yiming is expected to earn his first Olympic gold medal in men's snowboard slopestyle on Monday, after he finished on top in Sunday's qualifications to reach the final.